WEBVTT

0
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
Downloaded From www.AllSubs.org

1
00:00:06,240 --> 00:00:08,673
[TIRES SCREECH]

2
00:00:09,880 --> 00:00:13,599
GRUMPY: Three of a kind, let's do this.
CHUCKLES: That's it? Three guys?

3
00:00:14,760 --> 00:00:18,957
GRUMPY: Two guys on the roof. Every
guy gets a share. Five shares is plenty.

4
00:00:19,120 --> 00:00:22,475
CHUCKLES: Six shares. Don't
forget the guy who planned the job.

5
00:00:23,640 --> 00:00:26,835
GRUMPY: He thinks he can sit it out
and still take a slice.

6
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:30,992
- I know why they call him the Joker.
HAPPY: Why do they call him the Joker?

7
00:00:31,160 --> 00:00:33,912
DOPEY: I heard he wears makeup.
HAPPY: Makeup?

8
00:00:34,080 --> 00:00:36,957
DOPEY: Yeah, to scare people.
You know, war paint.

9
00:00:37,920 --> 00:00:40,831
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

10
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:45,072
GRUMPY: All right, everybody,
hands up, heads down!

11
00:00:46,440 --> 00:00:50,113
I said, hands up, heads down!

12
00:00:51,280 --> 00:00:55,113
Let's go, pal,
I'm making a withdrawal here.

13
00:00:56,360 --> 00:00:58,759
- I said, hands up!
- No!

14
00:00:59,120 --> 00:01:02,270
DOPEY:
Here comes the silent alarm.

15
00:01:03,440 --> 00:01:05,714
And there it goes.

16
00:01:06,880 --> 00:01:09,029
GRUMPY:
Heads down!

17
00:01:10,200 --> 00:01:13,430
All right, tootsie,
you're taking a dive with me.

18
00:01:14,600 --> 00:01:18,160
- Down! I said, stay down there!
WOMAN: Don't hurt me!

19
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:23,278
DOPEY: Funny, it didn't dial 911.
It was trying to reach a private number.

20
00:01:24,440 --> 00:01:27,271
HAPPY: Is it a problem?
DOPEY: No, I'm done here.

21
00:01:28,440 --> 00:01:30,555
[SILENCED GUNSHOT]

22
00:01:31,280 --> 00:01:34,555
GRUMPY:
Sit down! Down!

23
00:01:35,040 --> 00:01:38,110
Down! I said, stay down there!

24
00:01:39,200 --> 00:01:42,919
GRUMPY: Obviously we don't want you
doing anything with your hands...

25
00:01:43,080 --> 00:01:46,878
...other than holding on for dear life.

26
00:01:47,320 --> 00:01:50,231
CHUCKLES:
On the ground! Stay on the ground!

27
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:55,915
Nobody make a move!
Nobody! Stay down!

28
00:01:56,080 --> 00:01:58,559
[SHOTGUN BLAST]

29
00:01:59,320 --> 00:02:01,514
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLES]

30
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:04,669
Yeah!

31
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:08,391
You have any idea
who you're stealing from?

32
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:14,109
- You and your friends are dead.
GRUMPY: He's out, right?

33
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:17,915
[SHOTGUN BLAST]

34
00:02:18,080 --> 00:02:20,274
GRUMPY:
What...?

35
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:24,472
Where did you learn to count?

36
00:02:25,160 --> 00:02:28,116
HAPPY: They wired this thing up
with like 5000 volts.

37
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:31,474
What kind of bank does that?

38
00:02:32,640 --> 00:02:36,552
GRUMPY: A Mob bank.
I guess the Joker's as crazy as they say.

39
00:02:37,720 --> 00:02:39,709
Where's the alarm guy?

40
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:44,269
HAPPY: Boss told me when the guy
was done, I should take him out.

41
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:47,714
One less share, right?

42
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:51,750
GRUMPY:
Funny, he told me something similar.

43
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:55,319
HAPPY:
He what? No! No!

44
00:02:56,560 --> 00:02:58,879
GRUMPY:
That's a lot of money.

45
00:02:59,040 --> 00:03:03,589
If this Joker guy was so smart,
he'd have had us bring a bigger car.

46
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:06,795
[GUN COCKS]

47
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:12,714
I'm betting the Joker told you to kill me
soon as we loaded the cash.

48
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:18,229
BOZO:
No, no, no, I kill the bus driver.

49
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:21,989
GRUMPY:
Bus driver?

50
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:24,553
What bus driver?

51
00:03:25,480 --> 00:03:28,311
DRIVER:
School's out. Time to go.

52
00:03:29,480 --> 00:03:32,630
That guy's not getting up, is he?

53
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:35,952
That's a lot of money.

54
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:39,550
What happened to the rest of the guys?

55
00:03:40,040 --> 00:03:43,315
MANAGER:
You think you're smart, huh?

56
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:46,558
The guy that hired youse...

57
00:03:47,080 --> 00:03:50,548
...he'll just do the same to you.

58
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:55,673
Oh, criminals in this town
used to believe in things.

59
00:03:56,840 --> 00:03:59,068
Honor...

60
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:02,878
...respect.

61
00:04:03,040 --> 00:04:06,270
Look at you.
What do you believe in, huh?

62
00:04:07,440 --> 00:04:09,668
What do you believe in?!

63
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:15,710
I believe whatever doesn't kill you
simply makes you...

64
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:18,719
...stranger.

65
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:21,553
[ENGINE STARTS]

66
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:25,237
[MOANS]

67
00:04:26,520 --> 00:04:29,750
[CHILDREN CHATTERING]

68
00:04:30,760 --> 00:04:33,671
[SIRENS WAILING]

69
00:04:34,960 --> 00:04:38,758
MAN 1: <i>Mr. Mayor, you were elected</i>
<i>in a campaign to clean up the city.</i>

70
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:42,990
<i>- When are you gonna start?</i>
MAN 2: <i>I already have.</i>

71
00:04:43,160 --> 00:04:45,195
MAN 1: <i>Like this Batman.</i>

72
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:49,828
<i>We're hearing he's doing good,</i>
<i>criminals are running scared.</i>

73
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:54,549
- No, man. I don't like it tonight.
- What are you, superstitious?

74
00:04:55,720 --> 00:04:59,678
You got more chance of winning
the Powerball than running into him.

75
00:05:00,840 --> 00:05:05,071
<i>That's not true. Our men in the</i>
<i>Major Crimes Unit are close to an arrest.</i>

76
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:10,073
Hey, Wuertz, mayor says
you're closing in on the Batman.

77
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:14,276
The investigation is ongoing.

78
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:18,749
MAYOR: <i>The process of cleaning up</i>
<i>the streets is a long one.</i>

79
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:22,831
<i>I pledged in my campaign, uh, to have...</i>

80
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:26,195
Ever intending to see your wife again,
lieutenant?

81
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:30,920
I thought you had to
go look after your mother, detective.

82
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:33,957
Checked her back into the hospital.

83
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:36,958
I'm sorry.

84
00:05:37,440 --> 00:05:41,591
- So he hasn't shown up?
- He often doesn't.

85
00:05:42,960 --> 00:05:45,598
I like reminding everybody
he's out there.

86
00:05:46,760 --> 00:05:48,988
Why wouldn't he come?

87
00:05:49,320 --> 00:05:52,072
Hopefully...

88
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:56,039
...because he's busy.

89
00:05:57,240 --> 00:06:00,151
[TIRES SCREECHING]

90
00:06:01,080 --> 00:06:04,878
That's why we bring dogs.

91
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:08,270
- My little princes.
MAN: Please.

92
00:06:09,440 --> 00:06:13,876
Please, they're crawling in my mouth.
Please, I beg you, get them off.

93
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:17,679
CHECHEN: Look what your drugs
do to my customers.

94
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:21,398
SCARECROW:
Buyer beware.

95
00:06:22,560 --> 00:06:26,632
I told you my compound
would take you places.

96
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:31,439
I never said they'd be places
you wanted to go.

97
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:36,034
My business, repeat customers.

98
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:39,838
SCARECROW: You don't like
what I have to offer...

99
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:42,672
...you can buy from someone else.

100
00:06:43,840 --> 00:06:47,479
Assuming Batman left anyone
to buy from.

101
00:06:48,640 --> 00:06:51,471
[BARKING]

102
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:57,514
My dogs are hungry.

103
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:01,275
Pity there's only one of you.

104
00:07:02,640 --> 00:07:05,039
[THUG 1 YELLS]

105
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:08,789
[THUG 2 YELLS]

106
00:07:09,960 --> 00:07:12,234
[GUN COCKS]

107
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:16,512
CHECHEN: What...?
SCARECROW: That's not him.

108
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:20,392
Loose the dogs!

109
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:24,199
[SCREAMS]

110
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:28,079
SCARECROW:
That's more like it.

111
00:07:29,280 --> 00:07:32,236
[TIRES SCREECHING]

112
00:07:33,760 --> 00:07:36,671
[GRUNTING]

113
00:07:37,400 --> 00:07:39,628
[YELLING]

114
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:42,789
[DOG GROWLS]

115
00:07:43,960 --> 00:07:46,279
[YELLS]

116
00:07:47,120 --> 00:07:49,109
[DOG WHIMPERS]

117
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:52,912
[TIRES SCREECHING]

118
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:56,232
Don't let me find you out here again.

119
00:07:57,400 --> 00:08:01,119
- We're trying to help you.
BATMAN: I don't need help.

120
00:08:02,280 --> 00:08:04,554
Not my diagnosis.

121
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:10,156
What gives you the right? What's
the difference between you and me?

122
00:08:11,320 --> 00:08:15,073
I'm not wearing hockey pads.

123
00:08:16,440 --> 00:08:19,317
OFFICER:
Everybody back now!

124
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:23,232
[REPORTERS CLAMORING]

125
00:08:24,400 --> 00:08:28,437
He can't resist showing us his face.

126
00:08:29,520 --> 00:08:32,590
GORDON:
What's he hiding under that makeup?

127
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:36,560
RAMIREZ: Uh, can we get a minute,
people, please?

128
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:40,150
Him again. Who are the others?

129
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:43,833
Another bunch of smalltimers.

130
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,989
[DEVICE CLICKING]

131
00:08:46,160 --> 00:08:48,798
BATMAN:
Some of the marked bills I gave you.

132
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:53,155
My detectives have been
making drug buys with them.

133
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:57,788
This bank was another drop for the Mob.
That makes five.

134
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:02,428
- We found the bulk of their dirty cash.
- Time to move in.

135
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:08,229
We'd have to hit all banks
simultaneously. SWAT teams, backup.

136
00:09:09,560 --> 00:09:12,152
What about this Joker guy?

137
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:17,153
One man or the entire Mob? He can wait.

138
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:21,550
When the new DA hears about this,
he'll want in.

139
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:26,154
- Do you trust him?
- Be hard to keep him out.

140
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:31,630
I hear he's as stubborn as you are.

141
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:36,233
ALFRED:
Be nice when Wayne Manor's rebuilt.

142
00:09:37,400 --> 00:09:40,994
You can swap
not sleeping in a penthouse...

143
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:43,639
...for not sleeping in a mansion.

144
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:49,395
Whenever you stitch yourself up,
you do make a bloody mess.

145
00:09:50,560 --> 00:09:54,438
Yeah. It makes me learn
from my mistakes.

146
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:59,876
You ought to be pretty knowledgeable
by now, then.

147
00:10:00,520 --> 00:10:02,509
My armor.

148
00:10:03,680 --> 00:10:08,116
I'm carrying too much weight.
I need to be... I need to be faster.

149
00:10:09,280 --> 00:10:12,840
I'm sure Mr. Fox can oblige.

150
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:16,389
- Did you get mauled by a tiger?
- It was a dog.

151
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:20,994
- Huh?
- It was a big dog.

152
00:10:21,160 --> 00:10:25,869
There were more copycats last night,
Alfred, with guns.

153
00:10:26,040 --> 00:10:28,871
Why not hire them,
take the weekend off?

154
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:32,759
That wasn't exactly
what I had in mind...

155
00:10:33,920 --> 00:10:36,592
...when I said I wanted
to inspire people.

156
00:10:37,760 --> 00:10:40,591
I know.

157
00:10:41,760 --> 00:10:44,193
But things have improved.

158
00:10:45,400 --> 00:10:48,755
Look at the new district attorney.

159
00:10:49,400 --> 00:10:52,311
BRUCE:
I am, closely.

160
00:10:53,480 --> 00:10:56,311
Need to know if he can be trusted.

161
00:10:57,480 --> 00:11:02,359
Are you interested in his character
or his social circle?

162
00:11:03,040 --> 00:11:06,315
Who Rachel spends her time with
is her business.

163
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:10,190
I trust you don't have me followed
on my day off.

164
00:11:11,360 --> 00:11:14,351
If you ever took one, I might.

165
00:11:15,120 --> 00:11:17,917
Know your limits, Master Wayne.

166
00:11:18,080 --> 00:11:22,072
Batman has no limits.

167
00:11:23,240 --> 00:11:27,152
- Well, you do, sir.
- Well, can't afford to know them.

168
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:31,709
And what's gonna happen
on the day that you find out?

169
00:11:32,880 --> 00:11:36,474
We all know how much you like to say
"I told you so."

170
00:11:37,640 --> 00:11:41,837
On that day, Master Wayne,
even I won't want to.

171
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:44,399
Probably.

172
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:47,789
[DOOR OPENS]

173
00:11:48,960 --> 00:11:51,552
MAN:
Sorry I'm late, folks.

174
00:11:52,720 --> 00:11:54,709
[DOOR CLOSES]

175
00:11:55,320 --> 00:11:58,436
- Where were you?
- Worried you'd have to step up?

176
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:03,478
- Harvey, I know these briefs backwards.
- Well, then...

177
00:12:04,640 --> 00:12:07,551
...fair's fair.

178
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:11,676
Heads, I'll take it. Tails, he's all yours.

179
00:12:12,840 --> 00:12:15,831
Yeah? You wanna
flip a coin to see who leads?

180
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:20,276
My father's lucky coin. As I recall,
it got me my first date with you.

181
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:25,477
I wouldn't leave something like that
up to chance.

182
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:30,758
I don't. I make my own luck.

183
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:36,079
BAILIFF: All rise.
The Honorable Judge Freel presiding.

184
00:12:37,240 --> 00:12:40,800
I thought the DA just
played golf with the mayor.

185
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:46,509
Teeoff's 1:30. More than enough time
to put you away for life, Sally.

186
00:12:47,680 --> 00:12:50,159
With Carmine Falcone in Arkham...

187
00:12:51,320 --> 00:12:55,198
...someone must have stepped up
to run the so-called family.

188
00:12:56,040 --> 00:12:59,190
Is that man in this courtroom today?

189
00:13:00,680 --> 00:13:05,150
- Could you identify him for us, please?
- You win, counselor.

190
00:13:06,400 --> 00:13:08,833
It was me.

191
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:11,319
[CROWD LAUGHS]

192
00:13:12,480 --> 00:13:17,109
I have a sworn statement from you
that this man...

193
00:13:18,280 --> 00:13:22,829
...Salvatore Maroni, is the new head
of the Falcone crime family.

194
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:27,959
Maroni? He's a fall guy.
I'm the brains of the organization.

195
00:13:28,120 --> 00:13:30,109
[CROWD LAUGHS]

196
00:13:31,280 --> 00:13:33,759
JUDGE: Order.
- Permission to treat...

197
00:13:34,920 --> 00:13:37,114
...the witness as hostile?
- Granted.

198
00:13:38,280 --> 00:13:40,269
- Hostile? I'll show you hostile!

199
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:43,839
[CROWD GASPS]
[GUN CLICKS]

200
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:47,879
Carbon fiber, .28 caliber,
made in China.

201
00:13:48,040 --> 00:13:50,519
If you wanna kill a
public servant, Mr. Maroni...

202
00:13:51,680 --> 00:13:54,796
...I recommend you buy American.

203
00:13:55,680 --> 00:13:59,194
JUDGE: Get him out of here.
- But, Your Honor, I'm not done.

204
00:14:00,360 --> 00:14:03,590
[CROWD CHUCKLING
AND APPLAUDING]

205
00:14:04,760 --> 00:14:08,911
We'll never be able to link the gun
to Maroni, so we can't charge him.

206
00:14:09,080 --> 00:14:12,753
But they're trying to kill you,
means we're getting to them.

207
00:14:13,920 --> 00:14:17,912
I'm glad you're so pleased, Rachel.
I'm fine, by the way.

208
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:20,718
Come on, Harvey. You're Gotham's DA.

209
00:14:21,880 --> 00:14:25,599
You're not getting shot at,
you're not doing your job right.

210
00:14:26,760 --> 00:14:28,909
But, you know...

211
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:33,277
...if you said you were rattled,
we could take the rest of the day off.

212
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:38,238
Can't. I dragged the head of
the Major Crimes Unit down here.

213
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:44,951
Oh, Jim Gordon? He's a friend, actually.
Try to be nice.

214
00:14:45,640 --> 00:14:49,313
I hear you got a hell of a right cross.

215
00:14:50,480 --> 00:14:53,516
It's a shame Sal's going to walk.

216
00:14:54,680 --> 00:14:59,559
Yeah, well, good thing about the Mob
is they keep giving you second chances.

217
00:15:00,520 --> 00:15:03,750
Lightly irradiated bills.

218
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:07,395
Fancy stuff for a city cop. Have help?

219
00:15:08,840 --> 00:15:11,478
We liaise with various agencies...

220
00:15:12,640 --> 00:15:15,312
Save it, Gordon. I wanna meet him.

221
00:15:16,480 --> 00:15:20,916
Official policy is to arrest the vigilante
known as Batman on sight.

222
00:15:21,080 --> 00:15:24,150
Mm-hm. What about that floodlight
on the top of MCU?

223
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:28,629
If you got problems
with malfunctioning equipment...

224
00:15:29,800 --> 00:15:33,872
...I suggest you take them up
with Maintenance, counselor.

225
00:15:34,160 --> 00:15:37,594
I've put every money launderer
in Gotham behind bars...

226
00:15:38,760 --> 00:15:42,035
...but the Mob
is still getting its money out.

227
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:47,510
I think you and your friend
have found the last game in town.

228
00:15:48,680 --> 00:15:52,274
You're trying to hit them
where it hurts, their wallets.

229
00:15:53,440 --> 00:15:55,555
It's bold.

230
00:15:56,560 --> 00:15:58,549
You gonna count me in?

231
00:15:59,080 --> 00:16:03,311
In this town, the fewer people know
something, the safer the operation.

232
00:16:04,480 --> 00:16:07,630
I don't like that you got
your own special unit...

233
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:12,598
...and it's full of cops
I investigated at Internal Affairs.

234
00:16:13,760 --> 00:16:17,479
If I didn't work with cops
you'd investigated while at IA...

235
00:16:18,640 --> 00:16:20,834
...I'd be working alone.

236
00:16:21,560 --> 00:16:24,391
I don't get political points
for being an idealist.

237
00:16:25,560 --> 00:16:28,869
I do the best I can with what I have.

238
00:16:29,320 --> 00:16:33,915
You want me to back warrants
for search and seizure on five banks...

239
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:36,832
...without telling me what we're after.

240
00:16:37,880 --> 00:16:41,348
I can give you the names of the banks.

241
00:16:42,520 --> 00:16:45,351
Well, that's a start.

242
00:16:46,720 --> 00:16:49,950
I'll get you your warrants,
but I want your trust.

243
00:16:50,120 --> 00:16:52,712
Oh, you don't have
to sell me, Dent.

244
00:16:53,880 --> 00:16:56,791
We all know you're Gotham's
white knight.

245
00:16:57,000 --> 00:17:01,310
Yeah, well, I heard they have
a different name for me down at MCU.

246
00:17:02,880 --> 00:17:05,108
I wouldn't know about that.

247
00:17:06,240 --> 00:17:10,869
MAN: In China, Lau Security Investments
stands for dynamic new growth.

248
00:17:11,040 --> 00:17:16,158
A joint Chinese venture with
Wayne Enterprises will be a powerhouse.

249
00:17:17,320 --> 00:17:20,151
FOX:
Well, Mr. Lau...

250
00:17:21,520 --> 00:17:25,159
...I speak for the rest of the board...

251
00:17:26,720 --> 00:17:30,518
...and Mr. Wayne,
in expressing our own excitement.

252
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:35,670
Sir, I know Mr. Wayne is curious about
how his trust fund gets replenished...

253
00:17:36,840 --> 00:17:40,229
...but, frankly, this is embarrassing.

254
00:17:41,400 --> 00:17:44,868
You worry about the diligence,
Mr. Reese.

255
00:17:45,040 --> 00:17:48,235
I'll worry about Bruce Wayne.

256
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:51,879
It's done.

257
00:17:52,040 --> 00:17:54,712
The numbers are solid.

258
00:17:55,880 --> 00:17:58,359
Do them again.

259
00:17:59,520 --> 00:18:03,478
Wouldn't want the trust fund to run out,
now, would we?

260
00:18:04,160 --> 00:18:06,275
[SCOFFS]

261
00:18:07,080 --> 00:18:09,638
FOX:
Another long night?

262
00:18:10,800 --> 00:18:14,633
This joint venture was your idea,
and the consultants love it.

263
00:18:15,280 --> 00:18:17,474
But I'm not convinced.

264
00:18:18,640 --> 00:18:23,155
Lau's company has grown by
8 percent annually like clockwork.

265
00:18:24,320 --> 00:18:27,629
His revenue stream
must be off the books...

266
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:31,153
...maybe even illegal.

267
00:18:32,320 --> 00:18:34,912
Okay. Cancel the deal.

268
00:18:35,200 --> 00:18:37,315
You already knew.

269
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:41,434
Just needed a closer look at their books.

270
00:18:42,600 --> 00:18:45,556
Anything else you can trouble me for?

271
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:48,479
I need a new suit.

272
00:18:49,640 --> 00:18:53,029
Yeah. Three buttons
is a little '90s, Mr. Wayne.

273
00:18:54,200 --> 00:18:58,192
I'm not talking fashion, Mr. Fox,
so much as function.

274
00:18:59,200 --> 00:19:01,838
You wanna be able to turn your head.

275
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:04,991
Sure make backing out
of the driveway easier.

276
00:19:05,440 --> 00:19:07,919
I'll see what I can do.

277
00:19:08,480 --> 00:19:11,357
Took three weeks
to get a reservation here.

278
00:19:12,520 --> 00:19:15,556
I had to tell them
I work for the government.

279
00:19:16,720 --> 00:19:18,914
- Really?
- Health inspector's...

280
00:19:19,080 --> 00:19:21,274
...not afraid to pull strings.

281
00:19:22,440 --> 00:19:25,556
Rachel. Fancy that.

282
00:19:26,720 --> 00:19:30,109
Yeah, Bruce. Fancy that.

283
00:19:31,440 --> 00:19:34,510
Rachel, Natascha. Natascha, Rachel.

284
00:19:35,680 --> 00:19:41,834
- Natascha. Are you the prima...?
- Prima ballerina for the Moscow Ballet.

285
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:46,197
- Wow. Harvey's taking me next week.
- Really? So you're into ballet?

286
00:19:47,520 --> 00:19:50,590
Bruce. This is Harvey Dent.

287
00:19:51,920 --> 00:19:56,515
The famous Bruce Wayne.
Rachel's told me everything about you.

288
00:19:57,680 --> 00:19:59,829
I certainly hope not.

289
00:20:00,160 --> 00:20:04,357
- Let's put a couple tables together.
- I'm not sure that they'll let us.

290
00:20:05,520 --> 00:20:09,432
Oh, they should. I own the place.

291
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:14,713
How could you want to raise children
in a city like this?

292
00:20:15,880 --> 00:20:18,757
Well, I was raised here.
I turned out okay.

293
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:22,433
Is Wayne Manor in the city limits?

294
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:26,033
Is...? Heh-heh.

295
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:29,679
The Palisades? Sure.

296
00:20:30,840 --> 00:20:34,195
You know, as our new DA,
you might wanna figure out...

297
00:20:35,360 --> 00:20:38,112
...where your jurisdiction ends.

298
00:20:39,280 --> 00:20:44,068
I'm talking about the kind of city
that idolizes a masked vigilante.

299
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:49,471
Gotham City is proud of an ordinary
citizen standing up for what's right.

300
00:20:50,640 --> 00:20:53,790
Gotham needs heroes like you,
elected officials...

301
00:20:54,960 --> 00:20:57,837
...not a man who thinks
he's above the law.

302
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:00,115
Who appointed the Batman?

303
00:21:01,280 --> 00:21:05,955
We did. All of us who stood by
and let scum take control of our city.

304
00:21:06,120 --> 00:21:08,792
NATASCHA:
But this is a democracy, Harvey.

305
00:21:09,960 --> 00:21:12,632
DENT:
When their enemies were at the gates...

306
00:21:13,800 --> 00:21:18,349
...the Romans would suspend democracy
and appoint one man to protect the city.

307
00:21:19,520 --> 00:21:22,988
It wasn't considered an honor,
it was a public service.

308
00:21:23,160 --> 00:21:25,752
Harvey, the last man
that they appointed...

309
00:21:26,920 --> 00:21:30,115
...to protect the republic
was named Caesar...

310
00:21:31,280 --> 00:21:35,556
...and he never gave up his power.
- Okay, fine.

311
00:21:36,720 --> 00:21:38,994
You either die a hero...

312
00:21:39,160 --> 00:21:43,072
...or you live long enough
to see yourself become the villain.

313
00:21:44,240 --> 00:21:48,596
Whoever the Batman is, he doesn't
wanna do this for the rest of his life.

314
00:21:49,760 --> 00:21:53,877
How could he? Batman is looking for
someone to take up his mantle.

315
00:21:54,040 --> 00:21:57,235
NATASCHA:
Someone like you, Mr. Dent?

316
00:21:58,680 --> 00:22:02,035
Maybe. If I'm up to it.

317
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:09,228
What if Harvey Dent
is the Caped Crusader? Hm?

318
00:22:10,400 --> 00:22:14,437
If I were sneaking out every night,
someone would've noticed by now.

319
00:22:15,720 --> 00:22:20,679
Well, I'm sold, Dent,
and I'm gonna throw you a fundraiser.

320
00:22:21,840 --> 00:22:25,559
That's nice, but I'm not
up for reelection for three years.

321
00:22:26,720 --> 00:22:29,551
No, you don't understand.

322
00:22:30,720 --> 00:22:34,393
One fundraiser with my pals...

323
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:38,036
...you'll never need another cent.

324
00:22:39,800 --> 00:22:43,678
[METAL DETECTORS
BEEPING AND WHINING]

325
00:22:44,160 --> 00:22:47,196
What the hell is this?

326
00:22:48,480 --> 00:22:52,472
<i>As you're all aware,</i>
<i>one of our deposits was stolen.</i>

327
00:22:53,640 --> 00:22:57,871
<i>A relatively small amount, 68 million.</i>

328
00:22:58,040 --> 00:23:01,474
Who's stupid enough to steal from us?

329
00:23:02,800 --> 00:23:07,190
Two-bit wackjob,
wears a cheap purple suit and makeup.

330
00:23:08,360 --> 00:23:11,237
He's not the problem. He's a nobody.

331
00:23:12,400 --> 00:23:16,631
The problem is our money
being tracked by the cops.

332
00:23:17,800 --> 00:23:21,189
<i>Thanks to Mr. Maroni's</i>
<i>well-placed sources...</i>

333
00:23:22,360 --> 00:23:26,989
<i>... we know that police have indeed</i>
<i>identified our banks using marked bills...</i>

334
00:23:27,160 --> 00:23:30,549
<i>... and are planning to</i>
<i>seize your funds today.</i>

335
00:23:31,720 --> 00:23:36,554
<i>And since the enthusiastic new D A has</i>
<i>put all my competitors out of business...</i>

336
00:23:37,160 --> 00:23:41,516
<i>...I'm your only option.</i>
MARONl: <i>So, what are you proposing?</i>

337
00:23:42,680 --> 00:23:47,195
LAU: <i>Moving all deposits to</i>
<i>one secure location, not a bank.</i>

338
00:23:48,360 --> 00:23:51,237
- Where, then?
<i>- No one can know but me.</i>

339
00:23:52,960 --> 00:23:56,599
<i>If the police were to gain leverage</i>
<i>over one of you...</i>

340
00:23:57,760 --> 00:24:00,478
<i>... everyone's money would be at stake.</i>

341
00:24:01,640 --> 00:24:04,676
What stop them getting to you?

342
00:24:05,840 --> 00:24:09,798
<i>I go to Hong Kong,</i>
<i>far from Dent's jurisdiction...</i>

343
00:24:10,160 --> 00:24:13,913
<i>... and the Chinese will not extradite</i>
<i>one of their own.</i>

344
00:24:14,080 --> 00:24:16,638
MARONl:
<i>How soon can you move the money?</i>

345
00:24:17,920 --> 00:24:19,955
LAU:
<i>I already have.</i>

346
00:24:20,240 --> 00:24:23,754
For obvious reasons, I couldn't wait
for your permission.

347
00:24:24,360 --> 00:24:28,875
<i>Rest assured, your money is safe.</i>

348
00:24:29,080 --> 00:24:32,275
[JOKER LAUGHING]

349
00:24:33,760 --> 00:24:39,550
Oh, hee-hee, aha.
Ha, ooh, hee, ha-ha, ha-ha.

350
00:24:40,720 --> 00:24:43,870
And I thought my jokes were bad.

351
00:24:44,040 --> 00:24:47,998
Give me one reason why I shouldn't
have my boy pull your head off.

352
00:24:48,160 --> 00:24:50,388
How about a magic trick?

353
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:54,830
I'm gonna make this pencil disappear.

354
00:24:55,040 --> 00:24:57,109
Ta-da!

355
00:24:58,280 --> 00:25:00,713
It's...

356
00:25:01,880 --> 00:25:05,075
It's gone.

357
00:25:06,440 --> 00:25:09,670
Oh, and by the way,
the suit, it wasn't cheap.

358
00:25:10,840 --> 00:25:14,559
- You ought to know, you bought it.
CHECHEN: Sit.

359
00:25:15,600 --> 00:25:19,512
I want to hear proposition.

360
00:25:20,120 --> 00:25:23,509
JOKER:
Let's wind the clocks back a year.

361
00:25:24,840 --> 00:25:31,278
These cops and lawyers
wouldn't dare cross any of you.

362
00:25:32,400 --> 00:25:35,436
I mean, what happened?

363
00:25:36,600 --> 00:25:41,229
Did your balls drop off? Hm?

364
00:25:42,400 --> 00:25:45,356
You see, a guy like me...

365
00:25:46,800 --> 00:25:50,439
- A freak.
MOBSTER 1: Damn right.

366
00:25:51,600 --> 00:25:55,592
A guy like me... Look, listen.

367
00:25:56,120 --> 00:26:01,238
I know why you choose
to have your little, ahem...

368
00:26:02,400 --> 00:26:05,994
...group-therapy sessions
in broad daylight.

369
00:26:06,480 --> 00:26:10,153
I know why you're afraid
to go out at night.

370
00:26:11,280 --> 00:26:13,872
The Batman.

371
00:26:14,040 --> 00:26:20,068
See, Batman has shown Gotham
your true colors, unfortunately.

372
00:26:21,240 --> 00:26:25,596
Dent, he's just the beginning.

373
00:26:26,160 --> 00:26:31,711
And as for the television's
so-called plan...

374
00:26:32,160 --> 00:26:34,957
...Batman has no jurisdiction.

375
00:26:35,120 --> 00:26:38,588
He'll find him and make him squeal.

376
00:26:39,760 --> 00:26:43,638
I know the squealers when I see them...

377
00:26:44,800 --> 00:26:47,392
...and...

378
00:26:48,120 --> 00:26:50,553
CHECHEN:
What do you propose?

379
00:26:51,720 --> 00:26:55,029
It's simple. We, uh, kill the Batman.

380
00:26:56,200 --> 00:26:58,155
[MOBSTERS CHUCKLING]

381
00:26:59,320 --> 00:27:03,153
If it's so simple, why haven't
you done it already?

382
00:27:04,320 --> 00:27:07,914
If you're good at something,
never do it for free.

383
00:27:08,560 --> 00:27:10,788
How much you want?

384
00:27:11,480 --> 00:27:14,391
Uh, half.

385
00:27:15,560 --> 00:27:18,152
[MOBSTERS LAUGHING]

386
00:27:19,520 --> 00:27:23,159
GAMBOL: You're crazy.
- No, I'm not.

387
00:27:24,320 --> 00:27:27,356
No, I'm not.

388
00:27:28,880 --> 00:27:33,156
If we don't deal with this now...

389
00:27:34,320 --> 00:27:36,878
...soon...

390
00:27:37,080 --> 00:27:42,790
...little Gambol here won't be able
to get a nickel for his grandma.

391
00:27:43,440 --> 00:27:45,839
Enough from the clown!

392
00:27:46,000 --> 00:27:49,833
Ah, ta-ta-ta. Let's not blow...

393
00:27:50,000 --> 00:27:53,434
MOBSTER 2: Shit!
...this out of proportion.

394
00:27:54,600 --> 00:27:57,989
You think you can steal from us
and just walk away?

395
00:27:58,160 --> 00:28:00,639
- Yeah.
GAMBOL: I'm putting the word out.

396
00:28:01,800 --> 00:28:04,995
Five hundred grand for this clown dead.

397
00:28:05,160 --> 00:28:09,072
A million alive, so I can teach him
some manners first.

398
00:28:10,320 --> 00:28:13,788
All right. So, listen,
why don't you give me a call...

399
00:28:14,960 --> 00:28:19,555
...when you wanna start taking things
a little more seriously?

400
00:28:20,720 --> 00:28:23,517
Here's my card.

401
00:28:24,400 --> 00:28:27,356
Mm-mm.

402
00:28:28,800 --> 00:28:32,075
You're a hard man to reach.

403
00:28:33,960 --> 00:28:37,155
Lau's halfway to Hong Kong.

404
00:28:38,400 --> 00:28:42,119
If you'd have asked,
I could have taken his passport.

405
00:28:43,280 --> 00:28:46,840
All that was left in the vaults
were marked bills.

406
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:51,151
They knew we were coming.
As soon as your office got involved...

407
00:28:52,320 --> 00:28:54,309
My office?

408
00:28:55,480 --> 00:28:59,995
You're sitting down there with scum like
Wuertz and Ramirez and you're talking...

409
00:29:00,160 --> 00:29:04,152
Oh, yeah. I almost had your rookie
cold on a racketeering beat.

410
00:29:05,320 --> 00:29:10,677
Don't try and cloud the fact that clearly
Maroni's got people in your office, Dent.

411
00:29:11,360 --> 00:29:14,237
We need Lau back...

412
00:29:15,400 --> 00:29:20,188
...but the Chinese won't extradite
a national under any circumstances.

413
00:29:21,520 --> 00:29:25,114
If I get him to you,
can you get him to talk?

414
00:29:26,280 --> 00:29:28,429
I'll get him to sing.

415
00:29:29,600 --> 00:29:33,239
We're going after the Mob's life savings.

416
00:29:34,400 --> 00:29:36,594
Things will get ugly.

417
00:29:37,760 --> 00:29:40,955
I knew the risk when I took this job,
lieutenant.

418
00:29:41,120 --> 00:29:43,599
How will you get him back, any...?

419
00:29:44,080 --> 00:29:46,433
He does that.

420
00:29:47,600 --> 00:29:51,956
Our Chinese friends left town
before I could tell them the deal was off.

421
00:29:52,120 --> 00:29:56,476
Well, I'm sure that you've always
wanted to go to Hong Kong.

422
00:29:57,640 --> 00:30:00,710
What's wrong with a phone call?

423
00:30:01,880 --> 00:30:06,350
I think Mr. Lau deserves
a more personal touch.

424
00:30:07,520 --> 00:30:10,272
FOX: Now, for high-altitude jumps...

425
00:30:11,440 --> 00:30:15,113
...you're going to need oxygen
and stabilizers.

426
00:30:16,280 --> 00:30:20,750
Well, I must say,
compared to your usual requests...

427
00:30:21,920 --> 00:30:25,388
...jumping out of an airplane
is pretty straightforward.

428
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:29,036
BRUCE:
What about getting back into the plane?

429
00:30:30,200 --> 00:30:34,875
- I'd recommend a good travel agent.
- Without it landing.

430
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:38,639
Now, that's more like it, Mr. Wayne.

431
00:30:39,160 --> 00:30:42,674
The CIA had a program
back in the '60s...

432
00:30:43,840 --> 00:30:48,037
...for getting their people out
of hot spots called Sky Hook.

433
00:30:49,200 --> 00:30:52,760
- We could look into that.
- Yeah.

434
00:30:53,920 --> 00:30:56,512
Okay. Now...

435
00:30:57,960 --> 00:31:01,554
Hardened Kevlar plates
over titanium-dipped...

436
00:31:02,720 --> 00:31:05,756
...tri-weave fibers for flexibility.

437
00:31:06,920 --> 00:31:10,639
You'll be lighter, faster, more agile.

438
00:31:11,000 --> 00:31:14,070
Perhaps you should
read the instructions first?

439
00:31:15,240 --> 00:31:18,151
- Yeah.
- Now, there is a tradeoff.

440
00:31:19,320 --> 00:31:23,676
Separation of the plates makes you
more vulnerable to knives and gunfire.

441
00:31:24,840 --> 00:31:28,673
We wouldn't wanna make things
too easy, now, would we?

442
00:31:29,840 --> 00:31:32,796
How will it hold up against dogs?

443
00:31:33,960 --> 00:31:36,996
We talking rottweilers or Chihuahuas?

444
00:31:37,160 --> 00:31:40,549
Should do fine against cats.

445
00:31:41,720 --> 00:31:44,756
I found one in Arizona.

446
00:31:45,920 --> 00:31:49,718
A very nice man said he could have it
up and running in a week...

447
00:31:50,880 --> 00:31:52,915
...and he takes cash.

448
00:31:53,080 --> 00:31:56,799
- What about the flight crew?
- South Korean smugglers.

449
00:31:57,960 --> 00:32:01,076
They run flights into Pyongyang,
below radar.

450
00:32:02,240 --> 00:32:05,879
- Did you think of an alibi?
- Oh, yes.

451
00:32:06,880 --> 00:32:10,394
I believe this is your plane, sir.

452
00:32:11,440 --> 00:32:15,796
You look tired, Alfred.
You'll be all right without me?

453
00:32:16,400 --> 00:32:20,756
If you can tell me the Russian for
"apply your own bloody suntan lotion."

454
00:32:21,440 --> 00:32:26,115
Yo, Gambol, somebody here for you.
They say they've just killed the Joker.

455
00:32:27,280 --> 00:32:30,032
BOD YGUARD:
They brought the body.

456
00:32:31,760 --> 00:32:35,149
So, dead, that's 500.

457
00:32:36,040 --> 00:32:38,758
How about alive? Hm?

458
00:32:39,840 --> 00:32:43,877
You wanna know how I got these scars?

459
00:32:44,720 --> 00:32:48,598
My father was...

460
00:32:49,760 --> 00:32:52,159
...a drinker...

461
00:32:53,320 --> 00:32:55,514
...and a fiend.

462
00:32:56,320 --> 00:33:01,313
And one night,
he goes off crazier than usual.

463
00:33:02,720 --> 00:33:06,393
Mommy gets the kitchen knife
to defend herself.

464
00:33:07,560 --> 00:33:10,039
He doesn't like that...

465
00:33:11,200 --> 00:33:15,510
...not one bit.

466
00:33:16,680 --> 00:33:20,114
So, me watching...

467
00:33:21,280 --> 00:33:26,671
...he takes the knife to her,
laughing while he does it.

468
00:33:27,840 --> 00:33:31,798
He turns to me and he says:

469
00:33:32,960 --> 00:33:37,475
"Why so serious?"

470
00:33:38,720 --> 00:33:41,233
He comes at me with the knife.

471
00:33:42,880 --> 00:33:45,711
"Why so serious?"

472
00:33:46,880 --> 00:33:50,633
He sticks the blade in my mouth.

473
00:33:51,960 --> 00:33:56,714
"Let's put a smile on that face."

474
00:33:57,880 --> 00:34:00,996
And...

475
00:34:01,280 --> 00:34:03,759
Why so serious?

476
00:34:04,600 --> 00:34:07,033
Now...

477
00:34:08,200 --> 00:34:11,350
...our operation is small...

478
00:34:12,520 --> 00:34:16,318
...but there is a lot of potential...

479
00:34:17,480 --> 00:34:20,914
...for aggressive expansion.

480
00:34:21,080 --> 00:34:25,152
So which of you fine gentlemen
would like to join our team?

481
00:34:26,320 --> 00:34:31,552
Oh. There's only one spot open
right now, so we're gonna have...

482
00:34:32,200 --> 00:34:35,270
...tryouts.

483
00:34:36,680 --> 00:34:39,591
Make it fast.

484
00:34:40,640 --> 00:34:42,993
MAN:
Welcome to Hong Kong, Mr. Fox.

485
00:34:43,160 --> 00:34:46,754
Mr. Lau regrets he is unable
to greet you in person today.

486
00:34:47,920 --> 00:34:50,751
FOX:
I understand.

487
00:34:51,160 --> 00:34:55,596
For security purposes, I'm gonna have to
ask you to check in your mobile.

488
00:34:56,760 --> 00:34:59,273
Of course.

489
00:35:00,920 --> 00:35:05,469
I must apologize for leaving Gotham
in the middle of our negotiations.

490
00:35:06,640 --> 00:35:11,030
This misunderstanding
with the Gotham police force...

491
00:35:12,200 --> 00:35:15,634
...I couldn't let it threaten my company.
- Of course.

492
00:35:16,800 --> 00:35:20,837
A businessman of your stature
will understand and...

493
00:35:21,000 --> 00:35:25,788
...with you here now, we can continue.

494
00:35:26,960 --> 00:35:31,555
Well, I do appreciate you bringing me
out here in such style, Mr. Lau, but I re...

495
00:35:32,720 --> 00:35:34,869
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

496
00:35:35,040 --> 00:35:37,792
We do not allow cell phones in here.

497
00:35:38,960 --> 00:35:42,554
I'm sorry. Forgot I had it.

498
00:35:43,720 --> 00:35:49,157
No, I really came to tell you that
our business deal has to be put on hold.

499
00:35:50,680 --> 00:35:54,638
You see, we can't afford
to be seen to do business with...

500
00:35:55,720 --> 00:35:58,597
...whatever it is you're accused of being.

501
00:35:59,760 --> 00:36:03,228
I'm sure a businessman of your stature
will understand.

502
00:36:04,400 --> 00:36:09,154
I think, Mr. Fox, a simple phone call
might have sufficed.

503
00:36:10,320 --> 00:36:14,551
Mr. Wayne didn't want you to think
he was deliberately wasting your time.

504
00:36:15,720 --> 00:36:18,278
Just accidentally wasting it.

505
00:36:19,240 --> 00:36:24,233
That's very good, Mr. Lau.
"Accidentally." Very good.

506
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:27,274
Hey, sir.

507
00:36:28,760 --> 00:36:31,671
There's a better view
from the peak tram.

508
00:36:32,840 --> 00:36:35,592
How's the view from LSI Holdings?

509
00:36:36,880 --> 00:36:39,359
Restricted.

510
00:36:40,520 --> 00:36:43,431
Lau is holed up in there good and tight.

511
00:36:44,600 --> 00:36:47,431
- What's this?
- I had R & D work it up.

512
00:36:48,600 --> 00:36:51,192
Sends out a high-frequency pulse...

513
00:36:52,360 --> 00:36:56,079
...records the response time
for mapping an environment.

514
00:36:57,560 --> 00:37:01,028
Sonar. Just like a...

515
00:37:02,200 --> 00:37:05,270
Submarine, Mr. Wayne.
Like a submarine.

516
00:37:06,760 --> 00:37:09,512
- And the other device?
- It's in place.

517
00:37:10,400 --> 00:37:12,389
Mr. Wayne?

518
00:37:13,560 --> 00:37:15,788
Good luck.

519
00:37:16,120 --> 00:37:19,350
[SPEAKING IN CHINESE]

520
00:37:20,720 --> 00:37:23,631
[BEEPING]

521
00:37:24,320 --> 00:37:27,880
[SPEAKING IN CHINESE]

522
00:37:28,760 --> 00:37:31,239
[IN CHINESE]

523
00:37:32,680 --> 00:37:34,908
[GRUNTING]

524
00:37:35,680 --> 00:37:38,591
[SIRENS WAILING]

525
00:37:39,200 --> 00:37:42,111
[CHATTERING IN CHINESE]

526
00:37:43,160 --> 00:37:46,071
[LAU SHOUTING IN CHINESE]

527
00:37:47,840 --> 00:37:51,229
[ENGINES RUMBLING]

528
00:37:52,360 --> 00:37:56,397
RACHEL: Look, give us the money
and we'll talk about making a deal.

529
00:37:57,560 --> 00:38:01,711
The money is the only reason
I'm still alive.

530
00:38:02,880 --> 00:38:07,839
Oh, you mean, when they find out that
you've helped us, they're gonna kill you?

531
00:38:08,000 --> 00:38:10,638
- Are you threatening my client?
- No.

532
00:38:11,800 --> 00:38:16,839
I'm just assuming your client's
cooperation with this investigation.

533
00:38:17,400 --> 00:38:19,992
As will everyone.

534
00:38:20,280 --> 00:38:24,477
No? Okay.

535
00:38:25,920 --> 00:38:29,798
Enjoy your time in County, Mr. Lau.

536
00:38:30,960 --> 00:38:33,393
LAU:
Wait!

537
00:38:34,600 --> 00:38:37,511
I won't give you the money...

538
00:38:38,680 --> 00:38:42,558
...but I will give you my clients,
all of them.

539
00:38:43,840 --> 00:38:46,956
You were a glorified accountant.

540
00:38:47,120 --> 00:38:51,795
What could you possibly have
on all of them that we could charge?

541
00:38:52,960 --> 00:38:57,635
I'm good with calculation.
I handled all their investments.

542
00:38:58,800 --> 00:39:01,313
One big pot.

543
00:39:02,640 --> 00:39:04,914
Got it.

544
00:39:05,320 --> 00:39:08,072
One minute.

545
00:39:09,840 --> 00:39:13,434
RICO. If they pooled their money...

546
00:39:14,600 --> 00:39:17,318
...we can charge them
as one criminal conspiracy.

547
00:39:18,480 --> 00:39:20,595
Charge them with what?

548
00:39:21,760 --> 00:39:25,513
In a RICO case, if you can charge
one of them with a felony...

549
00:39:26,680 --> 00:39:30,148
You can charge all of them with it.
That's great.

550
00:39:31,480 --> 00:39:34,311
Mr. Lau.

551
00:39:35,280 --> 00:39:40,114
What kind of details do you have
about this communal fund?

552
00:39:41,280 --> 00:39:43,838
- Ledgers...?
- Immunity, protection...

553
00:39:44,000 --> 00:39:48,310
...a chartered plane back to Hong Kong.
- After you testify in open court.

554
00:39:49,480 --> 00:39:52,710
I'm just curious.
With all your clients locked up...

555
00:39:53,040 --> 00:39:56,156
...what's gonna happen
with all that money?

556
00:39:57,320 --> 00:40:01,312
Like I said, I'm good with calculation.

557
00:40:02,480 --> 00:40:07,951
He can't go to County.
I'll keep him here in the holding cells.

558
00:40:08,120 --> 00:40:11,554
What is this, Gordon, your fortress?

559
00:40:12,840 --> 00:40:16,400
Well, you trust them over at County?

560
00:40:17,560 --> 00:40:20,312
I don't trust them here.

561
00:40:21,000 --> 00:40:23,433
Lau stays.

562
00:40:24,880 --> 00:40:28,348
<i>Well, I don 't know about</i>
<i>Mr. Lau's travel arrangements...</i>

563
00:40:29,520 --> 00:40:32,238
<i>... but I'm sure glad he's back.</i>

564
00:40:33,400 --> 00:40:36,755
Put word out. We hire the clown.

565
00:40:37,440 --> 00:40:42,115
He was right.
We have to fix real problem.

566
00:40:43,600 --> 00:40:45,669
Batman.

567
00:40:46,040 --> 00:40:50,794
<i>- I'm not aware of any participation...</i>
- Our boy looks good on the tube.

568
00:40:51,280 --> 00:40:54,919
You sure you wanna embarrass me
in front of my friends?

569
00:40:55,080 --> 00:40:59,595
Oh, don't worry. They're coming too.

570
00:41:00,160 --> 00:41:02,912
STEPHENS:
Have a nice trip. See you next fall.

571
00:41:03,080 --> 00:41:05,832
WOMAN: <i>Seven hundred</i>
<i>twelve counts of extortion.</i>

572
00:41:06,000 --> 00:41:09,309
<i>Eight hundred and forty-nine</i>
<i>counts of racketeering.</i>

573
00:41:10,480 --> 00:41:13,914
Two hundred and forty-six
counts of fraud.

574
00:41:14,080 --> 00:41:17,799
Eighty-seven counts
of conspiracy murder.

575
00:41:18,680 --> 00:41:22,672
Five hundred and twenty-seven
counts of obstruction of justice.

576
00:41:23,080 --> 00:41:25,399
How do the defendants plead?

577
00:41:26,560 --> 00:41:30,279
[CLAMORING]

578
00:41:31,280 --> 00:41:33,269
Order in the court.

579
00:41:34,440 --> 00:41:37,829
MAYOR: <i>Five hundred and forty-nine</i>
<i>criminals at once.</i>

580
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:41,389
How did you convince Surrillo
to hear this farce?

581
00:41:42,560 --> 00:41:47,519
She shares my enthusiasm for justice.
After all, she is a judge.

582
00:41:48,680 --> 00:41:52,592
Even if you blow enough smoke
to get convictions out of Surrillo...

583
00:41:53,760 --> 00:41:57,228
...you're gonna set
a new record at appeals.

584
00:41:58,400 --> 00:42:01,789
It won't matter.
The head guys make bail, sure.

585
00:42:02,960 --> 00:42:06,269
But the midlevel guys, they can't.

586
00:42:07,440 --> 00:42:10,192
They can't afford to be off the streets.

587
00:42:11,360 --> 00:42:14,396
They'll cut deals that
include some jail time.

588
00:42:15,560 --> 00:42:19,438
Think of all you could do
with 18 months of clean streets.

589
00:42:20,920 --> 00:42:24,912
LOEB: Mr. Mayor, you can't...
- No, get out. Both of you.

590
00:42:25,920 --> 00:42:28,399
Sit down.

591
00:42:29,160 --> 00:42:33,038
The public likes you. That's the
only reason that this might fly.

592
00:42:34,200 --> 00:42:36,474
But that means it's on you.

593
00:42:37,640 --> 00:42:41,552
They're all gonna come after you now,
and not just the Mob.

594
00:42:42,720 --> 00:42:47,395
Politicians, journalists, cops.

595
00:42:48,560 --> 00:42:51,949
Anyone whose wallet's
about to get lighter.

596
00:42:52,120 --> 00:42:55,680
Are you up to it? You'd better be.

597
00:42:56,840 --> 00:42:59,876
Because they get anything on you...

598
00:43:00,040 --> 00:43:05,636
...and those criminals are back on the
streets, followed swiftly by you and me.

599
00:43:06,800 --> 00:43:09,028
Jesus!

600
00:43:10,320 --> 00:43:13,072
[SIRENS WAILING]

601
00:43:14,320 --> 00:43:17,675
ALFRED: I think your fundraiser
will be a great success, sir.

602
00:43:18,840 --> 00:43:22,400
BRUCE: And why do you think I wanna
hold a party for Harvey Dent?

603
00:43:23,560 --> 00:43:27,518
I assumed it was your usual reason
for socializing beyond myself...

604
00:43:28,680 --> 00:43:31,636
...and the scum of Gotham's underbelly:

605
00:43:32,800 --> 00:43:35,518
To try to impress Miss Dawes.

606
00:43:36,680 --> 00:43:41,593
Very droll, but very wrong.
Actually, it's Dent.

607
00:43:42,760 --> 00:43:46,513
ENGEL [ON TV]: <i>Police released video</i>
<i>footage found concealed on the body.</i>

608
00:43:47,680 --> 00:43:51,194
<i>Sensitive viewers, be aware.</i>
<i>The image is disturbing.</i>

609
00:43:52,360 --> 00:43:55,476
JOKER:
<i>Tell them your name.</i>

610
00:43:56,640 --> 00:43:59,232
<i>Brian Douglas.</i>

611
00:44:00,400 --> 00:44:02,594
[JOKER LAUGHS]

612
00:44:03,760 --> 00:44:06,990
JOKER:
<i>And are you the real Batman?</i>

613
00:44:07,160 --> 00:44:09,149
BRIAN: <i>No.</i>
JOKER: <i>No?</i>

614
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:13,197
<i>- No.</i>
<i>- No?</i>

615
00:44:14,360 --> 00:44:16,998
<i>Then why do you dress up like him?</i>

616
00:44:17,160 --> 00:44:19,309
[JOKER LAUGHS]

617
00:44:20,480 --> 00:44:22,469
<i>Whoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!</i>

618
00:44:23,640 --> 00:44:28,553
BRIAN: <i>Because he's a symbol that we</i>
<i>don 't have to be afraid of scum like you.</i>

619
00:44:29,720 --> 00:44:33,917
<i>Yeah. You do, Brian. You really do.</i>

620
00:44:34,080 --> 00:44:38,550
<i>Huh? Yeah. Oh, shh, shh, shh.</i>

621
00:44:39,720 --> 00:44:44,998
<i>So you think Batman 's</i>
<i>made Gotham a better place? Hm?</i>

622
00:44:45,200 --> 00:44:47,679
<i>Look at me.</i>

623
00:44:48,840 --> 00:44:52,035
<i>Look at me!</i>

624
00:44:53,640 --> 00:44:57,996
<i>You see, this is how crazy</i>
<i>Batman 's made Gotham.</i>

625
00:44:58,160 --> 00:45:01,355
<i>You want order in Gotham...</i>

626
00:45:02,680 --> 00:45:07,912
<i>... Batman must take off his mask</i>
<i>and turn himself in.</i>

627
00:45:08,080 --> 00:45:12,709
<i>Oh, and every day he doesn 't,</i>
<i>people will die.</i>

628
00:45:13,040 --> 00:45:16,076
<i>Starting tonight.</i>

629
00:45:17,480 --> 00:45:20,596
<i>I'm a man of my word.</i>

630
00:45:21,760 --> 00:45:24,113
[LAUGHING]

631
00:45:25,280 --> 00:45:27,872
[BRIAN SCREAMING]

632
00:45:28,240 --> 00:45:31,959
[CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING]

633
00:45:32,160 --> 00:45:35,879
Harvey Dent,
scourge of the underworld...

634
00:45:36,040 --> 00:45:39,998
...scared stiff by the trust-fund brigade.

635
00:45:40,160 --> 00:45:42,354
- I'll be back.
- Rachel.

636
00:45:43,520 --> 00:45:47,239
A little liquid courage, Mr. Dent?

637
00:45:48,400 --> 00:45:51,709
- Thank you. Alfred, right?
- That's right, sir.

638
00:45:52,880 --> 00:45:57,031
Rachel talks about you all the time.
You've known her her whole life.

639
00:45:58,200 --> 00:46:00,394
Not yet, sir.

640
00:46:01,600 --> 00:46:04,750
Any psychotic ex-boyfriends
I should be aware of?

641
00:46:05,920 --> 00:46:09,070
Oh, you have no idea.

642
00:46:10,240 --> 00:46:13,629
[HELICOPTER WHIRRING]

643
00:46:14,240 --> 00:46:16,593
BRUCE: I'm sorry that I'm late.

644
00:46:17,760 --> 00:46:21,035
I'm glad to see
that you all got started without me.

645
00:46:22,200 --> 00:46:26,749
Now, where is Harvey? Where...?

646
00:46:27,920 --> 00:46:31,229
Harvey Dent, the man of the hour.

647
00:46:32,400 --> 00:46:34,674
Where's Rachel Dawes?

648
00:46:35,840 --> 00:46:39,115
She is my oldest friend. Come here.

649
00:46:40,280 --> 00:46:43,669
When Rachel first told me she
was dating Harvey Dent...

650
00:46:44,840 --> 00:46:46,989
...I had one thing to say:

651
00:46:47,200 --> 00:46:50,509
"The guy from those God-awful
campaign commercials?"

652
00:46:51,680 --> 00:46:56,355
"I believe in Harvey Dent."
Yeah, nice slogan, Harvey.

653
00:46:57,520 --> 00:47:00,431
But it caught Rachel's attention.

654
00:47:01,600 --> 00:47:05,478
And then I started to pay attention
to Harvey...

655
00:47:06,880 --> 00:47:11,031
...and all that he's been doing
as our new DA.

656
00:47:12,200 --> 00:47:14,918
And you know what?

657
00:47:15,880 --> 00:47:18,313
I believe in Harvey Dent.

658
00:47:19,480 --> 00:47:23,916
I believe that on his watch,
Gotham can feel...

659
00:47:24,080 --> 00:47:28,595
...a little safer, a little more optimistic.

660
00:47:29,960 --> 00:47:35,112
Look at this face. This is the face
of Gotham's bright future.

661
00:47:36,280 --> 00:47:39,350
To Harvey Dent. Let's hear it for him.

662
00:47:40,720 --> 00:47:43,199
MAN:
Harvey.

663
00:47:44,320 --> 00:47:46,719
Harvey may not know you
well enough...

664
00:47:47,880 --> 00:47:50,757
...to understand you're
making fun of him...

665
00:47:51,920 --> 00:47:54,831
...but I do.
- No, I meant every word.

666
00:47:55,120 --> 00:47:58,918
You know that day
that you once told me about...

667
00:47:59,080 --> 00:48:02,071
...when Gotham would no longer
need Batman?

668
00:48:03,240 --> 00:48:06,071
- It's coming.
- Bruce.

669
00:48:07,880 --> 00:48:14,238
- You can't ask me to wait for that.
- It's happening now. Harvey is that hero.

670
00:48:15,400 --> 00:48:20,678
He locked up half of the city's criminals,
and he did it without wearing a mask.

671
00:48:21,840 --> 00:48:24,956
Gotham needs a hero with a face.

672
00:48:25,760 --> 00:48:28,955
DENT: You can throw a party, Wayne,
I'll give you that.

673
00:48:29,280 --> 00:48:32,111
Thanks again.

674
00:48:33,880 --> 00:48:36,518
You mind if I borrow Rachel?

675
00:48:37,840 --> 00:48:41,115
Lieutenant, that joker card
pinned to the body?

676
00:48:42,280 --> 00:48:44,952
Forensics found three sets of DNA.

677
00:48:45,120 --> 00:48:47,473
- Any matches?
- All three.

678
00:48:48,640 --> 00:48:52,996
The DNA belongs to Judge Surrillo,
Harvey Dent and Commissioner Loeb.

679
00:48:53,160 --> 00:48:56,071
The Joker's telling us
who he's targeting.

680
00:48:57,240 --> 00:49:00,993
Get a unit over to Surrillo's house.
Tell Wuertz to find Dent.

681
00:49:01,160 --> 00:49:04,116
Protective custody.
Where's the commissioner?

682
00:49:05,280 --> 00:49:07,713
- City hall.
- Seal the building.

683
00:49:08,880 --> 00:49:11,791
- No one in or out till I get there.
- Got it.

684
00:49:12,600 --> 00:49:15,875
Gordon. What are you up to?

685
00:49:16,040 --> 00:49:20,157
We're secure. I want a floor-by-floor
search of the entire building.

686
00:49:21,320 --> 00:49:24,788
We believe the Joker's
made a threat against your life.

687
00:49:25,960 --> 00:49:28,313
These are dangerous people.

688
00:49:29,480 --> 00:49:32,152
You're not giving me
a lot of information.

689
00:49:33,320 --> 00:49:36,197
Even we don't know
where you're going.

690
00:49:37,360 --> 00:49:41,557
Take the envelope, get in, open it.
It'll tell you where you're headed.

691
00:49:42,240 --> 00:49:45,071
You can't leave me alone
with these people.

692
00:49:46,240 --> 00:49:50,152
The whole Mob's after you
and you're worried about these guys?

693
00:49:51,320 --> 00:49:54,197
Compared to this,
the Mob doesn't scare me.

694
00:49:55,360 --> 00:49:59,796
Gordon, you're unlikely to discover this
for yourself, so...

695
00:50:00,960 --> 00:50:05,873
...take my word, the police commissioner
earns a lot of threats.

696
00:50:06,040 --> 00:50:12,353
I found the appropriate response
to these situations a long time ago.

697
00:50:13,560 --> 00:50:16,710
Them gunning for you
makes you see things clearly.

698
00:50:17,880 --> 00:50:20,154
Yeah, I bet.

699
00:50:21,320 --> 00:50:26,438
Yeah. It makes you think about things
you couldn't stand losing...

700
00:50:27,600 --> 00:50:30,511
...about who you wanna
spend your life with.

701
00:50:31,680 --> 00:50:35,558
- That's a pretty big commitment.
- Not if the Mob has their way.

702
00:50:36,560 --> 00:50:40,154
You get to explain to my wife...

703
00:50:41,040 --> 00:50:43,553
...why I'm late for dinner.

704
00:50:44,720 --> 00:50:48,757
Sir, the joker card
had traces of your DNA on it.

705
00:50:49,280 --> 00:50:52,794
- Don't do that.
- All right.

706
00:50:53,320 --> 00:50:57,118
- Let's be serious, then.
- Okay.

707
00:50:58,440 --> 00:51:00,429
What's your answer?

708
00:51:01,360 --> 00:51:03,793
I don't have an answer.

709
00:51:04,880 --> 00:51:06,869
How'd they get my DNA?

710
00:51:07,040 --> 00:51:10,110
Somebody with access
to your office or house...

711
00:51:11,280 --> 00:51:14,794
...must have lifted a tissue
or a glass... Wait! Wait!

712
00:51:15,960 --> 00:51:19,758
- Well, I guess no answer is a no.
- Harvey.

713
00:51:20,920 --> 00:51:23,956
- It's someone else, isn't it?
- Harvey.

714
00:51:24,120 --> 00:51:28,157
Just tell me it's not Wayne.
The guy's a complete f...

715
00:51:29,640 --> 00:51:32,039
What are you doing?

716
00:51:33,760 --> 00:51:35,749
GORDON:
Oh, shit.

717
00:51:36,920 --> 00:51:39,512
[LOEB COUGHING]

718
00:51:40,680 --> 00:51:43,352
GORDON:
Get a medic!

719
00:51:44,640 --> 00:51:46,709
They've come for him.

720
00:51:47,160 --> 00:51:49,275
We made it.

721
00:51:50,760 --> 00:51:52,749
Stay hidden.

722
00:51:53,920 --> 00:51:56,273
[SHOTGUN BLAST]

723
00:51:57,920 --> 00:52:02,117
Good evening, ladies and gentlemen.

724
00:52:03,920 --> 00:52:08,674
We are tonight's entertainment.

725
00:52:09,480 --> 00:52:12,710
I only have one question:

726
00:52:13,920 --> 00:52:18,310
Where is Harvey Dent?

727
00:52:19,400 --> 00:52:22,391
You know where Harvey is?
You know who he is?

728
00:52:23,560 --> 00:52:25,788
THUG:
Hands up, pretty boy.

729
00:52:26,960 --> 00:52:29,757
[THUG GRUNTING]

730
00:52:30,640 --> 00:52:34,313
Do you know where I can find Harvey?
I need to talk to him.

731
00:52:35,480 --> 00:52:39,199
Just something little, huh? No.

732
00:52:40,400 --> 00:52:44,039
What's going on out there? Wayne!

733
00:52:45,440 --> 00:52:47,759
Oh, thank God, you've
got a panic room.

734
00:52:48,920 --> 00:52:51,035
MAN: Hey, wait...

735
00:52:52,600 --> 00:52:55,318
Oh, you gotta be kidding me.

736
00:52:56,600 --> 00:52:59,511
You know, I'll settle for his loved ones.

737
00:53:00,680 --> 00:53:05,036
We're not intimidated by thugs.

738
00:53:06,960 --> 00:53:09,598
You know...

739
00:53:10,160 --> 00:53:14,038
...you remind me of my father.

740
00:53:15,480 --> 00:53:18,232
I hated my father.

741
00:53:19,400 --> 00:53:22,356
RACHEL:
Okay, stop.

742
00:53:23,040 --> 00:53:26,759
Well, hello, beautiful.

743
00:53:27,840 --> 00:53:32,515
You must be Harvey's squeeze. Hm?

744
00:53:33,880 --> 00:53:37,269
And you are beautiful.

745
00:53:38,920 --> 00:53:43,629
You look nervous. Is it the scars?

746
00:53:44,520 --> 00:53:47,636
You wanna know how I got them?

747
00:53:48,800 --> 00:53:52,234
Come here. Hey.

748
00:53:53,600 --> 00:53:56,238
Look at me.

749
00:53:57,680 --> 00:54:03,231
So I had a wife.
She was beautiful, like you...

750
00:54:04,480 --> 00:54:09,519
...who tells me I worry too much...

751
00:54:10,680 --> 00:54:14,478
...who tells me I ought to smile more...

752
00:54:15,640 --> 00:54:21,919
...who gambles and gets in deep
with the sharks. Hey.

753
00:54:22,320 --> 00:54:25,629
One day they carve her face.

754
00:54:26,120 --> 00:54:31,193
And we have no money for surgeries.
She can't take it.

755
00:54:32,560 --> 00:54:36,916
I just wanna see her smile again. Hm?

756
00:54:37,240 --> 00:54:41,038
I just want her to know
that I don't care about the scars.

757
00:54:42,560 --> 00:54:45,039
So...

758
00:54:46,600 --> 00:54:51,115
...I stick a razor in my mouth
and do this...

759
00:54:52,560 --> 00:54:54,879
...to myself.

760
00:54:55,160 --> 00:55:01,029
And you know what?
She can't stand the sight of me.

761
00:55:02,200 --> 00:55:04,679
She leaves.

762
00:55:05,360 --> 00:55:08,669
Now I see the funny side.

763
00:55:09,520 --> 00:55:12,033
Now I'm always smiling.

764
00:55:13,040 --> 00:55:16,110
[LAUGHS]

765
00:55:17,320 --> 00:55:21,517
You got a little fight in you. I like that.

766
00:55:22,680 --> 00:55:24,954
BATMAN:
Then you're gonna love me.

767
00:55:25,600 --> 00:55:28,511
[GRUNTING]

768
00:55:29,240 --> 00:55:31,229
[BATMAN YELLS]

769
00:55:32,960 --> 00:55:35,109
Drop the gun.

770
00:55:36,280 --> 00:55:39,794
Oh, sure. You just take off
your little mask...

771
00:55:40,960 --> 00:55:44,076
...and show us all who
you really are. Hm?

772
00:55:45,480 --> 00:55:47,629
Let her go.

773
00:55:48,400 --> 00:55:50,753
Very poor choice of words.

774
00:55:51,920 --> 00:55:53,909
[LAUGHS]

775
00:55:54,800 --> 00:55:57,597
[RACHEL SCREAMING]

776
00:55:58,640 --> 00:56:01,437
Are you all right?

777
00:56:02,600 --> 00:56:05,875
Let's not do that again.

778
00:56:06,160 --> 00:56:09,549
- Is Harvey okay?
- He's safe.

779
00:56:10,040 --> 00:56:12,314
Thank you.

780
00:56:13,640 --> 00:56:15,629
Jim, it's over.

781
00:56:16,800 --> 00:56:20,268
As long as they don't get to Lau,
we've cut off their funds.

782
00:56:21,440 --> 00:56:23,873
The prosecution's over.

783
00:56:24,040 --> 00:56:26,632
Nobody's standing up
in front of a judge...

784
00:56:27,800 --> 00:56:31,678
...while judges and police commissioners
are getting blown away.

785
00:56:32,840 --> 00:56:35,558
- What about Dent?
- He's got any sense...

786
00:56:36,720 --> 00:56:38,755
...Dent's halfway to Mex...

787
00:56:39,920 --> 00:56:42,433
DENT:
So where do you keep your trash?

788
00:56:43,720 --> 00:56:48,508
You're due in court. I need you alive
long enough to get you on the record.

789
00:56:49,680 --> 00:56:53,592
You can't protect me.
You can't even protect yourselves.

790
00:56:54,760 --> 00:56:58,957
You refuse to cooperate, you're not
coming back here, you go to County.

791
00:56:59,120 --> 00:57:02,475
How long do you calculate
you'll last in there?

792
00:57:03,840 --> 00:57:06,273
Targeting me won't get their money.

793
00:57:07,440 --> 00:57:10,192
I knew the Mob wouldn't go
down easily...

794
00:57:11,360 --> 00:57:14,351
...but this is different.
They crossed a line.

795
00:57:15,520 --> 00:57:17,714
You crossed the line first.

796
00:57:18,880 --> 00:57:23,156
You squeezed them, you hammered them
to the point of desperation.

797
00:57:24,320 --> 00:57:30,110
And in their desperation, they turned to
a man they didn't fully understand.

798
00:57:31,600 --> 00:57:35,034
Criminals aren't complicated, Alfred.

799
00:57:36,200 --> 00:57:39,316
We just need to figure out
what he's after.

800
00:57:40,480 --> 00:57:42,833
ALFRED:
With respect, Master Wayne...

801
00:57:43,000 --> 00:57:46,833
...perhaps this is a man
you don't fully understand either.

802
00:57:47,600 --> 00:57:51,194
A long time ago, I was in Burma...

803
00:57:52,360 --> 00:57:56,636
...and my friends and I were working
for the local government.

804
00:57:57,800 --> 00:58:01,268
They were trying to buy
the loyalty of tribal leaders...

805
00:58:02,440 --> 00:58:06,159
...by bribing them with
precious stones...

806
00:58:07,320 --> 00:58:12,711
...but their caravans were being raided
in a forest north of Rangoon by a bandit.

807
00:58:13,880 --> 00:58:18,031
So we went looking for the stones.

808
00:58:19,400 --> 00:58:25,315
But in six months, we never
met anyone who traded with him.

809
00:58:26,920 --> 00:58:31,754
One day, I saw a child
playing with a ruby...

810
00:58:32,920 --> 00:58:36,832
...the size of a tangerine.

811
00:58:37,080 --> 00:58:41,311
The bandit had been
throwing them away.

812
00:58:42,960 --> 00:58:46,554
- So why steal them?
- Because he thought it was good sport.

813
00:58:47,720 --> 00:58:53,475
Because some men aren't looking
for anything logical, like money.

814
00:58:54,640 --> 00:58:59,713
They can't be bought, bullied,
reasoned or negotiated with.

815
00:59:00,120 --> 00:59:04,795
Some men just wanna
watch the world burn.

816
00:59:05,720 --> 00:59:09,598
[VOICES SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

817
00:59:10,400 --> 00:59:12,515
WOMAN:
<i>Your name, sir?</i>

818
00:59:13,680 --> 00:59:17,717
JOKER: <i>Eighth and Orchard.</i>
<i>You'll find Harvey Dent there.</i>

819
00:59:18,080 --> 00:59:20,479
BATMAN:
Check the names.

820
00:59:21,800 --> 00:59:24,438
"Richard Dent."

821
00:59:25,560 --> 00:59:27,595
"Patrick Harvey."

822
00:59:28,880 --> 00:59:30,869
Harvey Dent.

823
00:59:31,040 --> 00:59:34,918
I need 10 minutes with the scene
before your men contaminate it.

824
00:59:35,120 --> 00:59:38,236
It's because of you
these guys are dead...

825
00:59:39,400 --> 00:59:41,879
Detective!

826
00:59:42,000 --> 00:59:44,956
Give us a minute, guys.

827
00:59:45,120 --> 00:59:47,633
That's brick underneath.

828
00:59:48,960 --> 00:59:51,552
Gonna take ballistics
off a shattered bullet?

829
00:59:52,720 --> 00:59:55,278
No.

830
00:59:56,680 --> 00:59:59,511
Fingerprints.

831
01:00:00,720 --> 01:00:03,551
Whatever you're gonna do, do it fast.

832
01:00:04,280 --> 01:00:09,796
Because we found his next target.
He's put it in tomorrow's paper.

833
01:00:10,400 --> 01:00:13,595
I'm not sure
you made it loud enough, sir.

834
01:00:14,160 --> 01:00:17,196
What can I do for you, Mr. Reese?

835
01:00:18,360 --> 01:00:22,989
You wanted me to do the diligence
on the LSI Holdings deal again.

836
01:00:23,640 --> 01:00:26,835
Well, I found some irregularities.

837
01:00:27,240 --> 01:00:30,231
Their CEO is in police custody.

838
01:00:31,400 --> 01:00:35,198
No, not with their numbers, with yours.

839
01:00:36,400 --> 01:00:40,358
Applied Sciences. Whole division
of Wayne Enterprises...

840
01:00:41,520 --> 01:00:44,112
...just disappeared overnight.

841
01:00:45,280 --> 01:00:50,353
I went down to the archives
and I started pulling some old files.

842
01:00:51,440 --> 01:00:54,237
Don't tell me you didn't
recognize your baby...

843
01:00:55,400 --> 01:00:59,870
...pancaking cop cars
on the evening news.

844
01:01:00,160 --> 01:01:04,232
Now you got the entire R & D
Department burning through cash...

845
01:01:05,400 --> 01:01:09,597
...claiming it's related to
cell phones for the Army?

846
01:01:10,760 --> 01:01:14,718
What are you building for him now,
a rocket ship?

847
01:01:15,520 --> 01:01:18,192
I want...

848
01:01:19,360 --> 01:01:24,114
...$ 10 million a year
for the rest of my life.

849
01:01:25,520 --> 01:01:28,556
Let me get this straight.

850
01:01:29,720 --> 01:01:33,075
You think that your client...

851
01:01:34,240 --> 01:01:38,198
One of the wealthiest,
most powerful men in the world...

852
01:01:39,360 --> 01:01:41,873
...is secretly a vigilante...

853
01:01:42,040 --> 01:01:47,511
...who spends his nights beating
criminals to a pulp with his bare hands...

854
01:01:48,680 --> 01:01:52,717
...and your plan
is to blackmail this person?

855
01:01:53,880 --> 01:01:56,108
Good luck.

856
01:01:57,880 --> 01:02:00,233
When...

857
01:02:01,600 --> 01:02:03,999
Keep that.

858
01:02:04,400 --> 01:02:07,755
FOX:
This is your original scan.

859
01:02:08,120 --> 01:02:11,315
Here it is reengineered.

860
01:02:12,200 --> 01:02:16,590
And there's the thumbprint he left
when he pushed the round in the clip.

861
01:02:17,520 --> 01:02:19,635
I'll get you a copy.

862
01:02:20,840 --> 01:02:25,469
Mr. Wayne, did you reassign R & D?

863
01:02:26,640 --> 01:02:30,029
Yeah. Government
telecommunications project.

864
01:02:31,200 --> 01:02:34,156
Wasn't aware
we had any government contracts.

865
01:02:35,400 --> 01:02:39,278
You know, Lucius, I'm playing this one
pretty close to the chest.

866
01:02:40,360 --> 01:02:42,998
Fair enough.

867
01:02:43,800 --> 01:02:46,199
ENGEL: With no word
from the Batman...

868
01:02:47,360 --> 01:02:49,793
...even as they mourn
Commissioner Loeb...

869
01:02:50,960 --> 01:02:55,191
...these cops have to wonder if
the Joker will make good on his threat...

870
01:02:56,360 --> 01:03:00,432
...in the obituary column of
<i>The Gotham Times</i> to kill the mayor.

871
01:03:01,160 --> 01:03:05,675
I've checked all the databases.
There are four possibles.

872
01:03:06,840 --> 01:03:09,876
Cross-reference the addresses.

873
01:03:10,040 --> 01:03:14,874
Look for Parkside,
overlooking the parade.

874
01:03:15,040 --> 01:03:17,109
I got one.

875
01:03:18,280 --> 01:03:23,114
Melvin White,
1502 Randolph Apartments.

876
01:03:24,480 --> 01:03:29,393
Aggravated assault,
moved to Arkham twice.

877
01:03:30,880 --> 01:03:33,393
What do you got on the roof?

878
01:03:34,560 --> 01:03:38,950
We're tight, but frankly,
there's a lot of windows up here.

879
01:03:39,160 --> 01:03:44,039
Commissioner Loeb dedicated his life
to law enforcement...

880
01:03:45,200 --> 01:03:48,395
...and to the protection
of his community.

881
01:03:49,560 --> 01:03:52,278
I remember when I first took office...

882
01:03:53,440 --> 01:03:56,874
...and I asked if he wanted
to stay on as commissioner.

883
01:03:57,040 --> 01:04:03,068
And he said he would, provided
I kept my politics out of his office.

884
01:04:04,680 --> 01:04:08,717
Clearly he was not a man who minced
words, nor should he have been.

885
01:04:09,840 --> 01:04:14,196
A number of policies that he enacted
as commissioner were unpopular.

886
01:04:15,360 --> 01:04:19,477
Policies that flooded my office
with angry calls and letters...

887
01:04:20,680 --> 01:04:23,272
- Who's that?
- What happened?

888
01:04:24,280 --> 01:04:27,077
They took our guns.

889
01:04:28,240 --> 01:04:30,958
And our uniforms.

890
01:04:31,120 --> 01:04:33,109
[TICKING]

891
01:04:34,280 --> 01:04:37,919
MAYOR: And as we recognize
the sacrifice of this man...

892
01:04:38,080 --> 01:04:42,868
...we must remember that vigilance
is the price of safety.

893
01:04:43,040 --> 01:04:46,429
Stand by. Honor guard.

894
01:04:47,600 --> 01:04:52,070
Attention. Port arms.

895
01:04:53,240 --> 01:04:58,438
Ready! Aim! Fire!

896
01:04:59,200 --> 01:05:01,679
Ready! Aim!

897
01:05:02,840 --> 01:05:05,114
[TIMER DINGS]

898
01:05:06,160 --> 01:05:09,435
Ready! Aim!

899
01:05:10,160 --> 01:05:12,912
[CROWD SCREAMING]

900
01:05:13,920 --> 01:05:16,353
[GUNSHOTS]

901
01:05:17,520 --> 01:05:19,873
OFFICER:
Stay down! Don't move!

902
01:05:20,640 --> 01:05:23,232
STEPHENS:
Mr. Mayor. Get him out of here.

903
01:05:24,080 --> 01:05:27,230
- I'll see you later.
- Why are you going back?

904
01:05:28,120 --> 01:05:30,519
[GUNSHOTS]

905
01:05:31,680 --> 01:05:34,193
[CROWD SCREAMING]

906
01:05:35,360 --> 01:05:37,349
Get out of here.

907
01:05:38,240 --> 01:05:40,912
Tell me what you know about the Joker.

908
01:05:41,360 --> 01:05:43,793
[CHUCKLING]

909
01:05:44,120 --> 01:05:46,314
[ENGINE STARTS]

910
01:05:47,680 --> 01:05:49,954
No.

911
01:05:50,360 --> 01:05:52,634
I'm sorry, Barbara.

912
01:05:53,520 --> 01:05:57,637
Jimmy, go play with your sister.
Go ahead, honey.

913
01:05:58,800 --> 01:06:01,950
STEPHENS: If there's anything
we can do, anything you need...

914
01:06:02,120 --> 01:06:04,792
...we're here for you.

915
01:06:05,960 --> 01:06:08,154
[BARBARA SOBBING]

916
01:06:09,320 --> 01:06:12,151
Shh.

917
01:06:13,320 --> 01:06:15,514
BARBARA:
Are you out there?

918
01:06:16,800 --> 01:06:22,112
Are you? You brought this
craziness on us. You did!

919
01:06:23,280 --> 01:06:26,555
You brought this on us!

920
01:06:27,560 --> 01:06:32,951
Switch it off, he ain't coming.
He doesn't wanna talk to us.

921
01:06:33,360 --> 01:06:37,238
God help whoever
he does wanna talk to.

922
01:06:38,640 --> 01:06:40,675
[DANCE MUSIC PLAYING]

923
01:06:41,840 --> 01:06:45,638
Can't we go someplace quieter?
We can't hear each other talk.

924
01:06:46,800 --> 01:06:50,519
What makes you think
I wanna hear you talk?

925
01:06:51,680 --> 01:06:53,669
What?

926
01:06:54,840 --> 01:06:57,068
[GRUNTING]

927
01:06:58,320 --> 01:07:01,038
[CROWD SCREAMING]

928
01:07:02,880 --> 01:07:05,438
- Yeah?
MAN: Second.

929
01:07:06,600 --> 01:07:08,589
Okay.

930
01:07:09,760 --> 01:07:12,830
- Harvey, where are you?
DENT: <i>Where are you?</i>

931
01:07:13,000 --> 01:07:16,036
I'm where you should be,
at Major Crimes.

932
01:07:17,200 --> 01:07:19,679
I'm trying to deal with all of this mess.

933
01:07:20,840 --> 01:07:25,276
- Can I get the fingerprint analysis?
<i>- Rachel, listen. You're not safe there.</i>

934
01:07:26,440 --> 01:07:29,158
- This is Gordon's unit.
<i>- Gordon 's gone.</i>

935
01:07:30,320 --> 01:07:34,756
RACHEL: He vouched for these men.
<i>- And he's gone.</i>

936
01:07:35,200 --> 01:07:38,191
<i>The Joker's named you next.</i>

937
01:07:39,360 --> 01:07:43,238
<i>God, is there someone, is there anyone</i>
<i>in this town we can trust?</i>

938
01:07:44,400 --> 01:07:47,038
Bruce.

939
01:07:48,320 --> 01:07:50,435
We can trust Bruce Wayne.

940
01:07:51,600 --> 01:07:54,113
<i>No. Rachel, I know</i>
<i>you're his friend, but...</i>

941
01:07:55,280 --> 01:07:58,032
Harvey, trust me.

942
01:07:59,200 --> 01:08:02,839
Bruce's penthouse is now
the safest place in the city.

943
01:08:03,000 --> 01:08:05,274
<i>Then you go straight there.</i>

944
01:08:06,440 --> 01:08:09,476
<i>Don 't tell anybody</i>
<i>and I'll find you there.</i>

945
01:08:10,640 --> 01:08:13,278
I love you.

946
01:08:14,720 --> 01:08:16,914
I want the Joker.

947
01:08:17,080 --> 01:08:19,672
From one professional to another...

948
01:08:20,840 --> 01:08:24,274
...you're trying to scare somebody,
pick a better spot.

949
01:08:25,440 --> 01:08:28,908
From this height,
the fall wouldn't kill me.

950
01:08:29,080 --> 01:08:31,593
- I'm counting on it.
- Huh!

951
01:08:32,760 --> 01:08:34,954
[SCREAMS]

952
01:08:35,120 --> 01:08:37,473
[BONE CRACKS]
[MARONI YELLS]

953
01:08:38,320 --> 01:08:41,470
[MARONI WHEEZING]

954
01:08:42,680 --> 01:08:46,672
- Where is he?
- I don't know where he is. He found us.

955
01:08:47,840 --> 01:08:50,068
He must have friends.

956
01:08:51,400 --> 01:08:54,595
Friends? Have you met this guy?

957
01:08:55,760 --> 01:08:58,273
Someone knows where he is.

958
01:08:59,440 --> 01:09:02,829
Nobody's gonna tell you nothing.

959
01:09:03,000 --> 01:09:05,274
They're wise to your act.

960
01:09:06,440 --> 01:09:11,274
You got rules.
The Joker, he's got no rules.

961
01:09:12,440 --> 01:09:18,116
Nobody's gonna cross him for you.
If you want this guy, you got one way.

962
01:09:19,280 --> 01:09:21,998
But you already know what that is.

963
01:09:22,160 --> 01:09:25,833
Just take off that mask,
let him come find you.

964
01:09:26,000 --> 01:09:28,194
[GROWLS]

965
01:09:29,400 --> 01:09:34,313
Or you can let a couple more people
get killed while you make up your mind.

966
01:09:35,920 --> 01:09:38,831
You wanna play games?

967
01:09:39,840 --> 01:09:42,319
[GUNSHOT]

968
01:09:43,880 --> 01:09:45,869
How's that feel?

969
01:09:46,040 --> 01:09:49,554
- You wouldn't.
- I wouldn't!

970
01:09:50,000 --> 01:09:52,558
- You don't think I will?
- Mm-mm.

971
01:09:53,720 --> 01:09:56,676
- You don't think I will?
- Mm-mm.

972
01:09:57,000 --> 01:10:01,072
No. No, I wouldn't.

973
01:10:02,240 --> 01:10:05,674
That's why I'm not
gonna leave it up to me.

974
01:10:06,640 --> 01:10:10,518
Heads, you get to keep your head.

975
01:10:11,920 --> 01:10:14,478
Tails...

976
01:10:15,400 --> 01:10:17,389
...not so lucky.

977
01:10:18,760 --> 01:10:23,150
So you wanna tell me about the Joker?

978
01:10:24,640 --> 01:10:27,392
[THUG CHUCKLES]

979
01:10:28,160 --> 01:10:32,709
- Let's go again.
- I don't know anything! God, don't!

980
01:10:33,880 --> 01:10:37,155
You're not playing the odds, friend.

981
01:10:38,240 --> 01:10:41,151
Let's do it again.

982
01:10:42,880 --> 01:10:45,632
You'd leave a man's life to chance?

983
01:10:46,360 --> 01:10:50,796
- Not exactly.
- His name's Schiff, Thomas.

984
01:10:51,960 --> 01:10:55,838
He's a paranoid schizophrenic,
former patient at Arkham.

985
01:10:56,000 --> 01:11:01,437
The kind of mind the Joker attracts.
What do you expect to learn from him?

986
01:11:02,640 --> 01:11:06,313
The Joker killed Gordon.
He's gonna kill Rachel.

987
01:11:07,480 --> 01:11:11,153
You're the symbol of hope
I could never be.

988
01:11:12,320 --> 01:11:15,072
Your stand against organized crime...

989
01:11:16,240 --> 01:11:20,312
...is the first legitimate ray of light
in Gotham in decades.

990
01:11:21,480 --> 01:11:25,950
If anyone saw this,
everything would be undone.

991
01:11:26,120 --> 01:11:29,315
The criminals you arrested
would be released...

992
01:11:30,480 --> 01:11:34,438
...and Jim Gordon
will have died for nothing.

993
01:11:35,040 --> 01:11:38,190
You're gonna hold
a press conference tomorrow.

994
01:11:39,360 --> 01:11:42,635
- Why?
- No one else will die because of me.

995
01:11:43,800 --> 01:11:47,030
Gotham's in your hands now.

996
01:11:48,200 --> 01:11:50,838
You can't.

997
01:11:51,000 --> 01:11:53,319
You can't give in.

998
01:11:54,600 --> 01:11:58,034
You can't give in!

999
01:11:59,760 --> 01:12:01,954
Harvey called.

1000
01:12:02,120 --> 01:12:06,032
He said Batman's gonna turn himself in.

1001
01:12:07,200 --> 01:12:09,269
I have no choice.

1002
01:12:10,440 --> 01:12:14,398
You honestly think that's gonna
keep the Joker from killing people?

1003
01:12:15,560 --> 01:12:19,870
Maybe not. But I have enough blood
on my hands.

1004
01:12:20,320 --> 01:12:25,950
And I've seen now what I would
have to become to stop men like him.

1005
01:12:26,480 --> 01:12:30,790
You once told me that
if the day came when I was finished...

1006
01:12:31,960 --> 01:12:34,951
...that we'd be together.

1007
01:12:35,640 --> 01:12:39,677
Bruce, don't make me
your one hope for a normal life.

1008
01:12:40,160 --> 01:12:42,434
Did you mean it?

1009
01:12:43,880 --> 01:12:46,632
Yes.

1010
01:12:47,200 --> 01:12:49,918
Bruce.

1011
01:12:50,840 --> 01:12:55,594
If you turn yourself in,
they're not gonna let us be together.

1012
01:12:56,800 --> 01:13:00,633
ALFRED: Logs as well?
BRUCE: Everything.

1013
01:13:01,800 --> 01:13:06,031
Anything that could lead back
to Lucius or Rachel.

1014
01:13:07,160 --> 01:13:11,311
People are dying, Alfred.
What would you have me do?

1015
01:13:12,480 --> 01:13:17,075
Endure, Master Wayne. Take it.

1016
01:13:18,240 --> 01:13:22,789
They'll hate you for it,
but that's the point of Batman.

1017
01:13:23,960 --> 01:13:30,273
He can be the outcast. He can make
the choice that no one else can make.

1018
01:13:31,440 --> 01:13:33,714
The right choice.

1019
01:13:34,200 --> 01:13:38,112
No, today I found out
what Batman can't do.

1020
01:13:39,280 --> 01:13:41,474
He can't endure this.

1021
01:13:42,760 --> 01:13:46,513
Today you get to say "I told you so."

1022
01:13:47,080 --> 01:13:51,117
Today, I don't want to.

1023
01:13:52,720 --> 01:13:55,119
But I did bloody tell you.

1024
01:13:56,280 --> 01:13:58,554
[BRUCE CHUCKLES]

1025
01:13:59,040 --> 01:14:02,918
ALFRED: I suppose they're gonna
lock me up as well...

1026
01:14:03,680 --> 01:14:05,874
...as your accomplice.

1027
01:14:06,040 --> 01:14:11,591
BRUCE: Accomplice? I'm gonna tell them
the whole thing was your idea.

1028
01:14:12,680 --> 01:14:17,070
Ladies and gentlemen, I've called
this press conference for two reasons.

1029
01:14:18,240 --> 01:14:21,196
Firstly, to assure the citizens
of Gotham...

1030
01:14:22,360 --> 01:14:26,875
...that everything that can be done
over the Joker killings is being done.

1031
01:14:27,040 --> 01:14:29,029
[CHATTERING]

1032
01:14:30,200 --> 01:14:34,158
Secondly, because the Batman
has offered to turn himself in.

1033
01:14:35,320 --> 01:14:37,958
<i>But let's consider the situation.</i>

1034
01:14:38,320 --> 01:14:41,834
Should we give in
to this terrorist's demands?

1035
01:14:42,000 --> 01:14:44,399
Do we really think he's gonna...?

1036
01:14:45,560 --> 01:14:49,791
You'd rather protect an outlaw vigilante
than the lives of citizens?

1037
01:14:50,960 --> 01:14:54,235
The Batman is an outlaw.

1038
01:14:55,080 --> 01:14:57,911
That's not why we demand
he turn himself in...

1039
01:14:58,080 --> 01:15:00,672
...we're doing it because we're scared.

1040
01:15:01,840 --> 01:15:05,513
We've been happy to let Batman
clean up our streets till now.

1041
01:15:06,680 --> 01:15:10,513
MAN 1: Things are worse than ever!
MAN 2: Amen.

1042
01:15:11,800 --> 01:15:14,631
Yes, they are.

1043
01:15:15,040 --> 01:15:18,918
But the night is darkest
just before the dawn.

1044
01:15:19,280 --> 01:15:22,271
And I promise you...

1045
01:15:23,040 --> 01:15:25,393
...the dawn is coming.

1046
01:15:26,560 --> 01:15:31,917
One day, the Batman will have to answer
for the laws he's broken. But to us...

1047
01:15:32,080 --> 01:15:34,752
...not to this madman.

1048
01:15:35,920 --> 01:15:39,150
- No more dead cops!
OFFICERS: Yeah!

1049
01:15:40,320 --> 01:15:42,833
He should turn himself in!

1050
01:15:43,000 --> 01:15:46,594
MAN 3: Give us the Batman! Come on!
MAN 4: Where is he?

1051
01:15:47,360 --> 01:15:50,430
So be it. Take the Batman into custody.

1052
01:15:51,880 --> 01:15:54,757
WOMAN: What?
MAN 5: Is he here?

1053
01:15:55,440 --> 01:15:57,429
I am the Batman.

1054
01:15:58,760 --> 01:16:02,638
MAN 6: What?
MAN 7: Come on.

1055
01:16:03,680 --> 01:16:06,511
RACHEL:
Alfred.

1056
01:16:07,800 --> 01:16:10,518
Why is he letting Harvey do this?

1057
01:16:11,680 --> 01:16:15,558
- He went down to the press conference.
- I know. He just stood by.

1058
01:16:16,720 --> 01:16:19,711
Perhaps both Bruce and Mr. Dent...

1059
01:16:20,880 --> 01:16:24,758
...believe that Batman stands for
something more important...

1060
01:16:25,920 --> 01:16:29,150
...than the whims of a terrorist,
Miss Dawes...

1061
01:16:30,320 --> 01:16:33,231
...even if everyone hates him for it.

1062
01:16:34,400 --> 01:16:37,436
That's the sacrifice he's making.

1063
01:16:38,600 --> 01:16:43,070
He's not being a hero.
He's being something more.

1064
01:16:44,600 --> 01:16:47,158
Yeah, you're absolutely right.

1065
01:16:48,320 --> 01:16:52,278
Letting Harvey take the fall for this
is not heroic at all.

1066
01:16:53,840 --> 01:16:56,398
You know him better than anyone.

1067
01:16:57,800 --> 01:16:59,789
I do.

1068
01:17:00,040 --> 01:17:03,952
Will you give this to him for me?
When the time is right?

1069
01:17:04,360 --> 01:17:06,509
How will I know?

1070
01:17:07,680 --> 01:17:10,113
It's not sealed.

1071
01:17:11,480 --> 01:17:13,959
Goodbye, Alfred.

1072
01:17:14,960 --> 01:17:17,632
Bye, Rachel.

1073
01:17:18,040 --> 01:17:20,155
[CELL DOOR OPENS]

1074
01:17:21,200 --> 01:17:23,952
I didn't have time to talk this through.

1075
01:17:24,120 --> 01:17:26,314
What are you doing?

1076
01:17:27,480 --> 01:17:30,471
They're transferring me
to Central Holding.

1077
01:17:31,760 --> 01:17:36,275
This is the Joker's chance, and when he
attacks, the Batman will take him down.

1078
01:17:37,440 --> 01:17:39,919
Listen. This is too dangerous.

1079
01:17:40,080 --> 01:17:44,629
We get this guy to County, he's their
problem. The streets will be cleared...

1080
01:17:45,800 --> 01:17:50,349
...so let's go.
The convoys stop for no reason.

1081
01:17:51,520 --> 01:17:53,919
I hope you got some moves, pal.

1082
01:17:54,080 --> 01:17:57,878
He's using you as bait. He doesn't
know if he can get the Joker.

1083
01:17:58,040 --> 01:18:00,075
He's failed so far.

1084
01:18:01,400 --> 01:18:03,879
How do you know
what he's thinking?

1085
01:18:04,040 --> 01:18:07,270
I just do. Anyway,
this isn't just about you.

1086
01:18:08,440 --> 01:18:11,192
What about the people
depending on you...

1087
01:18:12,360 --> 01:18:16,238
...to clean the city up
and do it honorably and...?

1088
01:18:17,680 --> 01:18:21,194
Harvey. Tell everyone the truth.

1089
01:18:22,560 --> 01:18:25,357
Heads, I go through with it.

1090
01:18:26,560 --> 01:18:29,391
This is your life. You can't leave...

1091
01:18:30,560 --> 01:18:33,835
...something like that to chance.
- I'm not.

1092
01:18:34,480 --> 01:18:36,833
[ENGINE STARTS]

1093
01:18:37,000 --> 01:18:40,309
You make your own luck.

1094
01:18:41,600 --> 01:18:44,352
[TRUCK HORN BLARING]

1095
01:18:45,240 --> 01:18:48,151
Hey, you wait like everybody else, pal.

1096
01:18:49,480 --> 01:18:52,710
What the hell is that?

1097
01:18:53,880 --> 01:18:56,996
Obstruction ahead, obstruction ahead!

1098
01:18:57,160 --> 01:19:01,232
Damn it! All units divert down
onto Lower Fifth. I repeat, exit down.

1099
01:19:02,640 --> 01:19:04,709
<i>Exit down!</i>

1100
01:19:05,880 --> 01:19:09,110
Lower Fifth? We'll be
like turkeys on Thanksgiving.

1101
01:19:10,480 --> 01:19:13,710
Jesus. Come on, get us out of here.
Let's go.

1102
01:19:14,800 --> 01:19:18,075
Listen, we need backup.
We've got company.

1103
01:19:19,240 --> 01:19:21,719
We got trouble, guys.

1104
01:19:22,520 --> 01:19:24,555
Lock and load!

1105
01:19:25,640 --> 01:19:28,517
[TIRES SCREECHING]

1106
01:19:29,200 --> 01:19:32,077
[CAR HORNS HONKING]

1107
01:19:33,320 --> 01:19:35,639
The hell was that?

1108
01:19:36,600 --> 01:19:40,160
- These are built for that, right?
- He'll need something...

1109
01:19:41,320 --> 01:19:44,038
...a lot bigger to get through this.

1110
01:19:45,040 --> 01:19:47,439
What is that?

1111
01:19:48,720 --> 01:19:50,994
What is that, a bazooka?

1112
01:19:51,280 --> 01:19:53,918
I didn't sign up for this!

1113
01:19:54,600 --> 01:19:56,874
Look out.

1114
01:19:57,640 --> 01:19:59,755
Look out!

1115
01:20:00,720 --> 01:20:02,709
JOKER:
Hmm.

1116
01:20:03,120 --> 01:20:05,189
Come on, let's go!

1117
01:20:06,880 --> 01:20:09,518
[CONSOLE BEEPING]

1118
01:20:10,960 --> 01:20:13,279
[EXPLOSION]

1119
01:20:14,880 --> 01:20:17,996
Harvey, Harvey, Harvey Dent.

1120
01:20:18,160 --> 01:20:21,879
Oh, excuse me. I wanna drive.

1121
01:20:22,600 --> 01:20:27,036
COMPUTER: <i>Scanning all systems.</i>
<i>Scanning all systems.</i>

1122
01:20:28,080 --> 01:20:30,991
[JOKER HUMMING]

1123
01:20:31,200 --> 01:20:34,236
We gotta get topside.
We need air support, now!

1124
01:20:35,520 --> 01:20:38,317
I like this job. I like it.

1125
01:20:39,480 --> 01:20:42,994
COMPUTER: <i>Damage catastrophic.</i>
<i>Eject sequence initiated.</i>

1126
